        "content": "title:\t[A3] Trace mode for evaluation\nstate:\tOPEN\nauthor:\tkonard (Konstantin Diachenko)\nlabels:\tarea:diagnostics, enhancement, phase:A\ncomments:\t0\nassignees:\t\nprojects:\t\nmilestone:\t\nnumber:\t30\n--\n## Motivation\nWithout a step-by-step trace it is impossible to teach the engine, debug operator-redefinition pitfalls, or build a derivation tree later.\n\n## Goal\n`--trace` flag prints every reduction step, operator resolution, and assignment lookup with span info.\n\n## LiNo Surface\n```\n$ rml --trace demo.lino\n[span demo.lino:3:1] resolve (and: avg)\n[span demo.lino:5:1] eval (a = a) → assigned 1\n```\n\n## API Surface\nCLI flag `--trace` in both `js/` and `rust/` runners; library-level option `trace: true`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Trace output is reproducible (no nondeterminism).\n- [ ] Tests verify trace lines for representative programs.\n- [ ] Documented in `docs/DIAGNOSTICS.md`.\n\n## References\n- Source case study: [`docs/case-studies/issue-26/`](https://github.com/link-foundation/relative-meta-logic/tree/main/docs/case-studies/issue-26)\n- Comparison docs: [CONCEPTS-COMPARISION.md](https://github.com/link-foundation/relative-meta-logic/blob/main/docs/CONCEPTS-COMPARISION.md), [FEATURE-COMPARISION.md](https://github.com/link-foundation/relative-meta-logic/blob/main/docs/FEATURE-COMPARISION.md)\n- Planning issue: #26\n\n## Dependencies\n- Depends on: #28\n- Blocks: #35\n\n## Out of Scope\nTime-travel debugging or step-back; trace-driven proof export (planned for phase C).\n\n---\n_Plan ID: **A3**, phase **A**. Filed automatically from the case study under `docs/case-studies/issue-26/issue-plan.md` (PR #27)._",
