        "type": "text",
        "text": "This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user provided GitHub issue #30 (https://github.com/link-foundation/relative-meta-logic/issues/30) titled \"[A3] Trace mode for evaluation\" to solve. Requirements:\n   - Add `--trace` flag to both `js/` and `rust/` CLI runners\n   - Add library-level option `trace: true`\n   - Print every reduction step, operator resolution, and assignment lookup with span info\n   - Format like `[span demo.lino:3:1] resolve (and: avg)` and `[span demo.lino:5:1] eval (a = a) → assigned 1`\n   - Trace output must be reproducible (deterministic)\n   - Tests verify trace lines for representative programs\n   - Documented in `docs/DIAGNOSTICS.md`\n   - Update existing PR #101 (currently draft/WIP) on branch `issue-30-fbacf7f8954b`\n   - Working directory: `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1777477820370`\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - Relative Meta-Logic (RML) over LiNo (Links Notation)\n   - Many-valued logic (binary, ternary, fuzzy, probabilistic)\n   - Two parallel implementations: JavaScript (js/src/rml-links.mjs) and Rust (rust/src/lib.rs)\n   - Structured Diagnostics with error codes (E001-E006), spans (file/line/col/length)\n   - AST evaluation with operator resolution (and, or, not, =, !=, both, neither)\n   - Probability assignments via `((expr) has probability p)`\n   - Operator redefinition via `(name: ...)` form\n   - LiNo parser via `links-notation` crate/package\n   - Top-level form span tracking via `computeFormSpans()` / `compute_form_spans()`\n   - Panic-to-Diagnostic conversion in Rust (decode_panic_payload)\n   - Trace event kinds: `resolve`, `assign`, `lookup`, `eval`\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1777477820370/rust/src/lib.rs** (heavily modified)\n     - Added `TraceEvent` struct, `format_trace_event`, `format_trace_value` helpers near the top\n     - Added trace fields to `Env`: `trace_enabled: bool`, `trace_events: Vec<TraceEvent>`, `current_span: Option<Span>`, `default_span: Span`\n     - Added `trace()` method on `Env`\n     - Changed `apply_eq` and `apply_neq` from `&self` to `&mut self` (so they can emit lookup events)\n     - Changed `apply_named_op_on_nodes` helper to take `&mut Env` and clone op before calling\n     - Added trace event in assignment branch:\n       ```rust\n       env.trace(\"assign\", format!(\"{} ← {}\", key, format_trace_value(clamped)));\n       ```\n     - Added resolve trace events in `define_form` for both `Op::Compose` and `Aggregator` selection\n     - Added `EvaluateResult.trace: Vec<TraceEvent>` field\n     - Added `EvaluateOptions { env, trace }` struct\n     - Added `evaluate_with_options` function — emits eval event per top-level form with summary `<form-key> → query <v>`, `type <t>`, or just value\n     - Refactored `evaluate` to delegate to `evaluate_with_options` (backwards compatible)\n     - Updated `compute_form_spans` to handle inline comments after `)`+whitespace (mirrors JS fix using `last_closing_depth_zero_col` and `saw_ws_after_close` state)\n\n   - **/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1777477820370/rust/src/main.rs** (rewritten)\n     - Parses `--trace` flag, calls `evaluate_with_options`, prints trace events to stderr via `format_trace_event`\n     ```rust\n     use rml::{evaluate_with_options, format_diagnostic, format_trace_event, EvaluateOptions, RunResult};\n     // ...\n     let mut trace = false;\n     for arg in args.iter().skip(1) {\n         if arg == \"--trace\" { trace = true; } else { positionals.push(arg.clone()); }\n     }\n     let evaluation = evaluate_with_options(&text, Some(file), EvaluateOptions { env: None, trace });\n     if trace {\n         for event in &evaluation.trace { eprintln!(\"{}\", format_trace_event(event)); }\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1777477820370/js/tests/trace.test.mjs** (created)\n     - 10 tests covering: trace omitted by default, deterministic across runs, correct event kinds, span tracking for resolve/assign/lookup/eval, formatTraceEvent output, and `<input>` fallback when no file\n     - Uses a 6-form `DEMO` constant matching the Rust counterpart\n\n   - **/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1777477820370/rust/tests/trace_tests.rs** (created)\n     - 10 mirrored tests: `evaluate_without_trace_returns_empty_trace`, `evaluate_with_trace_returns_non_empty_trace`, `trace_is_deterministic_across_runs`, `trace_does_not_affect_results_or_diagnostics`, `resolve_event_for_aggregator_redef`, `assign_event_for_probability_form`, `lookup_event_when_assigned_equality_fires`, `eval_event_per_top_level_form`, `format_trace_event_renders_span_kind_detail`, `format_trace_event_falls_back_to_input_when_no_file`\n\n   - **/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1777477820370/docs/DIAGNOSTICS.md** (extended)\n     - Added \"Trace mode\" section covering CLI flag (--trace), JS API (`evaluate(source, { trace: true })`), Rust API (`evaluate_with_options` with `EvaluateOptions { env, trace }`), output format `[span <file>:<line>:<col>] <kind> <details>`, an example trace from demo.lino, event kinds table (resolve/assign/lookup/eval), and a determinism note\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   - **Rust borrow checker error** at line 1251: `cannot borrow env as mutable because it is also borrowed as immutable` in `env.clamp(env.apply_neq(...))`. Fixed by extracting to a local: `let neq = env.apply_neq(&children[0], &children[2]); return EvalResult::Value(env.clamp(neq));`\n   - Initial confusion about working directory in cargo commands — resolved by confirming pwd was already `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1777477820370/rust`\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - Designed unified trace event format `[span <file>:<line>:<col>] <kind> <details>` matching the issue's example output\n   - Identified four trace event kinds: `resolve`, `assign`, `lookup`, `eval`\n   - For Rust: chose to put trace state directly on Env (rather than closures) to avoid lifetime/borrow complexities. Used `&mut Env` propagation through `apply_eq`/`apply_neq`.\n   - Made trace deterministic: Rust output diff'd against JS output on examples/demo.lino — 18 lines, identical\n   - Cross-runtime parity verified: both implementations produce the same trace lines for demo.lino\n   - Test counts verified: Rust 264 tests pass (10 new trace + 242 existing + 10 diagnostics + 2 shared), JS 434 tests pass (10 new trace + 424 existing)\n\n6. All user messages:\n   - System-reminder messages providing file content reminders, deferred tools list, available skills, and user context (email: deep.assistant.team@proton.me, date: 2026-04-29)\n   - **\"Tool loaded.\"** — confirmation after I called ToolSearch to load Task* tools\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - Task #7: Update PR #101 with description and ready-for-review (`gh pr edit`, `gh pr ready 101`)\n   - Also: Commit all changes to branch `issue-30-fbacf7f8954b`, push to remote\n\n8. Current Work:\n   Just completed Task #6 by writing the new \"Trace mode\" section to `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1777477820370/docs/DIAGNOSTICS.md`. This appended after the existing \"Adding a new code\" section. The section includes:\n   - CLI usage examples for both runners\n   - Library API examples for both JS and Rust\n   - Output format specification with example from demo.lino\n   - Event kinds table (resolve/assign/lookup/eval with description of when each fires)\n   - Determinism note explaining trace reproducibility\n   \n   All implementation is done and tests pass:\n   - JS: 434 tests pass (10 new trace tests in js/tests/trace.test.mjs)\n   - Rust: 264 tests pass (10 new trace tests in rust/tests/trace_tests.rs)\n   - Cross-runtime parity verified by running both CLIs on examples/demo.lino — output matches exactly\n\n   Task tracker state at this point:\n   - #1 [completed] Understand existing JS evaluator and trace points\n   - #2 [completed] Understand Rust evaluator and trace points\n   - #3 [completed] Implement --trace flag and library option in JS\n   - #4 [completed] Implement --trace flag in Rust runner\n   - #5 [completed] Add JS and Rust trace tests\n   - #6 [in_progress] Document trace mode in docs/DIAGNOSTICS.md (just completed via Edit, needs status flip)\n   - #7 [pending] Update PR 101 with description and ready-for-review\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Mark Task #6 as completed via TaskUpdate, then proceed to Task #7: commit all changes to `issue-30-fbacf7f8954b`, push to remote, update PR #101 description with a summary of the trace mode feature, before/after demonstration, and mark the PR ready for review with `gh pr ready 101`. The commit should bundle the Rust implementation (rust/src/lib.rs, rust/src/main.rs), the new trace test files (js/tests/trace.test.mjs, rust/tests/trace_tests.rs), and the docs update (docs/DIAGNOSTICS.md). This directly continues the workflow from the original task: \"When you finish implementation, use gh pr ready 101.\"\n\nIf you need specific details from before compaction (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /home/box/.claude/projects/-tmp-gh-issue-solver-1777477820370/28a784f8-3dce-46c6-bfe0-3826da2572a7.jsonl\nContinue the conversation from where it left off without asking the user any further questions. Resume directly — do not acknowledge the summary, do not recap what was happening, do not preface with \"I'll continue\" or similar. Pick up the last task as if the break never happened."
